<dd><p>Ordinary least squares Linear Regression.</p>
<p>LinearRegression fits a linear model with coefficients w =3D (w1, =E2=80=
=A6, wp)
to minimize the residual sum of squares between the observed targets in
the dataset, and the targets predicted by the linear approximation.</p>
<dl class=3D"field-list">
<dt class=3D"field-odd">Parameters<span class=3D"colon">:</span></dt>
<dd class=3D"field-odd"><dl>
<dt><strong>fit_intercept</strong><span class=3D"classifier">bool, default=
=3DTrue</span></dt><dd><p>Whether to calculate the intercept for this model=
. If set
to False, no intercept will be used in calculations
(i.e. data is expected to be centered).</p>
</dd>
<dt><strong>copy_X</strong><span class=3D"classifier">bool, default=3DTrue<=
/span></dt><dd><p>If True, X will be copied; else, it may be overwritten.</=
p>
</dd>
<dt><strong>tol</strong><span class=3D"classifier">float, default=3D1e-6</s=
pan></dt><dd><p>The precision of the solution (<code class=3D"docutils lite=
ral notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">coef_</span></code>) is determined by =
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">tol</span>=
</code> which
specifies a different convergence criterion for the <code class=3D"docutils=
 literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">lsqr</span></code> solver.
<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">tol</span>=
</code> is set as <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=
=3D"pre">atol</span></code> and <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate=
