Please check the <a class=3D"reference internal" href=3D"https://scikit-lea=
rn.org/stable/metadata_routing.html#metadata-routing"><span class=3D"std st=
d-ref">User Guide</span></a> on how the routing
mechanism works.</p>
<p>The options for each parameter are:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">Tru=
e</span></code>: metadata is requested, and passed to <code class=3D"docuti=
ls literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">score</span></code> if provided=
. The request is ignored if metadata is not provided.</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">Fal=
se</span></code>: metadata is not requested and the meta-estimator will not=
 pass it to <code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre=
">score</span></code>.</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">Non=
e</span></code>: metadata is not requested, and the meta-estimator will rai=
se an error if the user provides it.</p></li>
<li><p><code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D"pre">str=
</span></code>: metadata should be passed to the meta-estimator with this g=
iven alias instead of the original name.</p></li>
</ul>
<p>The default (<code class=3D"docutils literal notranslate"><span class=3D=
"pre">sklearn.utils.metadata_routing.UNCHANGED</span></code>) retains the
existing request. This allows you to change the request for some
parameters and not others.</p>
